<p>
  TitleLeaf allows a publisher to offer free library processing for all orders or
  <a href="/guides/settings/free-processing-minimum">free library processing for orders exceeding a certain dollar amount</a>.
  The following procedure outlines how to setup the former.
</p>

<ol>

  <li>
    <p>Navigate to the Library Processing section of the Settings page.</p>
    <p>
      <%= cdn_image "titleleaf-menu-settings.png", alt: "Titleleaf Menu Settings" %>
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>Set <em>Free Library Processing</em> to <em>Yes</em>.</p>
    <p>
      <%= cdn_image "titleleaf-settings-free-library-processing.png", alt: "Titleleaf Settings Free Library Processing" %>
    </p>
    <p>
      Note: The <em>Free Library Processing Minimum</em> value will be ignored
      but to avoid confusion for other administrators erase any pre-existing
      dollar amount from it.
    </p>
  </li>

  <li>
    <p>Click the <em>Save</em> button at the bottom of the Settings page.</p>
  </li>

</ol>
